#: ../../../api/adapt.rst:2
msgid "`adapt` -- Types adaptation"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../api/adapt.rst:6
msgid ""
"The `!psycopg.adapt` module exposes a set of objects useful for the "
"configuration of *data adaptation*, which is the conversion of Python "
"objects to PostgreSQL data types and back."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../api/adapt.rst:10
msgid ""
"These objects are useful if you need to configure data adaptation, i.e. if "
"you need to change the default way that Psycopg converts between types or if "
"you want to adapt custom data types and objects. You don't need this object "
"in the normal use of Psycopg."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../api/adapt.rst:15
msgid "See :ref:`adaptation` for an overview of the Psycopg adaptation system."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../api/adapt.rst:21
msgid "Dumpers and loaders"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.14/site-packages/psycopg/adapt.py:docstring
#: of psycopg.adapt.Dumper:1
msgid "Convert Python object of the type `!cls` to PostgreSQL representation."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../api/adapt.rst:25
msgid ""
"This is an `abstract base class`_, partially implementing the `~psycopg.abc."
"Dumper` protocol. Subclasses *must* at least implement the `.dump()` method "
"and optionally override other members."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.14/site-packages/psycopg/adapt.py:docstring
#: of psycopg.adapt.Dumper.dump:1
msgid "Convert the object `!obj` to PostgreSQL representation."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.14/site-packages/psycopg/_adapters_map.py:docstring
#: of psycopg._adapters_map.AdaptersMap.register_dumper:0
#: psycopg._adapters_map.AdaptersMap.register_loader:0 ../../../api/adapt.rst:0
msgid "Parameters"
msgstr "參數"

#: ../../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.14/site-packages/psycopg/adapt.py:docstring
#: of psycopg.adapt.Dumper.dump:3
msgid "the object to convert."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../api/adapt.rst:33
msgid ""
"`!dump()` can also return `!None`, to represent a :sql:`NULL` in the "
"database."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../api/adapt.rst:40
msgid ""
"Class attribute. Set it to `~psycopg.pq.Format.BINARY` if the class `dump()` "
"methods converts the object to binary format."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.14/site-packages/psycopg/adapt.py:docstring
#: of psycopg.adapt.Dumper.quote:1
msgid ""
"By default return the `dump()` value quoted and sanitised, so that the "
"result can be used to build a SQL string. This works well for most types and "
"you won't likely have to implement this method in a subclass."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.14/site-packages/psycopg/adapt.py:docstring
#: of psycopg.adapt.Dumper.get_key:1
msgid ""
"Implementation of the `~psycopg.abc.Dumper.get_key()` member of the "
"`~psycopg.abc.Dumper` protocol. Look at its definition for details."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.14/site-packages/psycopg/adapt.py:docstring
#: of psycopg.adapt.Dumper.get_key:4
msgid ""
"This implementation returns the `!cls` passed in the constructor. Subclasses "
"needing to specialise the PostgreSQL type according to the *value* of the "
"object dumped (not only according to to its type) should override this class."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.14/site-packages/psycopg/adapt.py:docstring
#: of psycopg.adapt.Dumper.upgrade:1
msgid ""
"Implementation of the `~psycopg.abc.Dumper.upgrade()` member of the "
"`~psycopg.abc.Dumper` protocol. Look at its definition for details."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.14/site-packages/psycopg/adapt.py:docstring
#: of psycopg.adapt.Dumper.upgrade:4
msgid ""
"This implementation just returns `!self`. If a subclass implements "
"`get_key()` it should probably override `!upgrade()` too."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.14/site-packages/psycopg/adapt.py:docstring
#: of psycopg.adapt.Loader:1
msgid "Convert PostgreSQL values with type OID `!oid` to Python objects."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../api/adapt.rst:52
msgid ""
"This is an `abstract base class`_, partially implementing the `~psycopg.abc."
"Loader` protocol. Subclasses *must* at least implement the `.load()` method "
"and optionally override other members."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.14/site-packages/psycopg/adapt.py:docstring
#: of psycopg.adapt.Loader.load:1
msgid "Convert a PostgreSQL value to a Python object."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../api/adapt.rst:62
msgid ""
"Class attribute. Set it to `~psycopg.pq.Format.BINARY` if the class `load()` "
"methods converts the object from binary format."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../api/adapt.rst:67
msgid "Other objects used in adaptations"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.14/site-packages/psycopg/adapt.py:docstring
#: of psycopg.adapt.PyFormat:1
msgid "Enum representing the format wanted for a query argument."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.14/site-packages/psycopg/adapt.py:docstring
#: of psycopg.adapt.PyFormat:3
msgid ""
"The value `AUTO` allows psycopg to choose the best format for a certain "
"parameter."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.14/site-packages/psycopg/adapt.py:docstring
#: of psycopg.adapt.AdaptersMap:1
msgid ""
"Establish how types should be converted between Python and PostgreSQL in an "
"`~psycopg.abc.AdaptContext`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.14/site-packages/psycopg/adapt.py:docstring
#: of psycopg.adapt.AdaptersMap:4
msgid ""
"`!AdaptersMap` maps Python types to `~psycopg.adapt.Dumper` classes to "
"define how Python types are converted to PostgreSQL, and maps OIDs to "
"`~psycopg.adapt.Loader` classes to establish how query results are converted "
"to Python."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.14/site-packages/psycopg/adapt.py:docstring
#: of psycopg.adapt.AdaptersMap:9
msgid ""
"Every `!AdaptContext` object has an underlying `!AdaptersMap` defining how "
"types are converted in that context, exposed as the `~psycopg.abc."
"AdaptContext.adapters` attribute: changing such map allows to customise "
"adaptation in a context without changing separated contexts."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.14/site-packages/psycopg/adapt.py:docstring
#: of psycopg.adapt.AdaptersMap:14
msgid ""
"When a context is created from another context (for instance when a "
"`~psycopg.Cursor` is created from a `~psycopg.Connection`), the parent's `!"
"adapters` are used as template for the child's `!adapters`, so that every "
"cursor created from the same connection use the connection's types "
"configuration, but separate connections have independent mappings."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.14/site-packages/psycopg/adapt.py:docstring
#: of psycopg.adapt.AdaptersMap:20
msgid ""
"Once created, `!AdaptersMap` are independent. This means that objects "
"already created are not affected if a wider scope (e.g. the global one) is "
"changed."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.14/site-packages/psycopg/adapt.py:docstring
#: of psycopg.adapt.AdaptersMap:24
msgid ""
"The connections adapters are initialised using a global `!AdptersMap` "
"template, exposed as `psycopg.adapters`: changing such mapping allows to "
"customise the type mapping for every connections created afterwards."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.14/site-packages/psycopg/adapt.py:docstring
#: of psycopg.adapt.AdaptersMap:28
msgid ""
"The object can start empty or copy from another object of the same class. "
"Copies are copy-on-write: if the maps are updated make a copy. This way "
"extending e.g. global map by a connection or a connection map from a cursor "
"is cheap: a copy is only made on customisation."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../api/adapt.rst:75
msgid ":ref:`adaptation` for an explanation about how contexts are connected."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.14/site-packages/psycopg/_adapters_map.py:docstring
#: of psycopg._adapters_map.AdaptersMap.register_dumper:1
msgid ""
"Configure the context to use `!dumper` to convert objects of type `!cls`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.14/site-packages/psycopg/_adapters_map.py:docstring
#: of psycopg._adapters_map.AdaptersMap.register_dumper:3
msgid ""
"If two dumpers with different `~Dumper.format` are registered for the same "
"type, the last one registered will be chosen when the query doesn't specify "
"a format (i.e. when the value is used with a ``%s`` \"`~PyFormat.AUTO`\" "
"placeholder)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.14/site-packages/psycopg/_adapters_map.py:docstring
#: of psycopg._adapters_map.AdaptersMap.register_dumper:8
msgid "The type to manage."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.14/site-packages/psycopg/_adapters_map.py:docstring
#: of psycopg._adapters_map.AdaptersMap.register_dumper:9
msgid "The dumper to register for `!cls`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.14/site-packages/psycopg/_adapters_map.py:docstring
#: of psycopg._adapters_map.AdaptersMap.register_dumper:11
msgid ""
"If `!cls` is specified as string it will be lazy-loaded, so that it will be "
"possible to register it without importing it before. In this case it should "
"be the fully qualified name of the object (e.g. ``\"uuid.UUID\"``)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.14/site-packages/psycopg/_adapters_map.py:docstring
#: of psycopg._adapters_map.AdaptersMap.register_dumper:16
msgid ""
"If `!cls` is None, only use the dumper when looking up using "
"`get_dumper_by_oid()`, which happens when we know the Postgres type to adapt "
"to, but not the Python type that will be adapted (e.g. in COPY after using "
"`~psycopg.Copy.set_types()`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.14/site-packages/psycopg/_adapters_map.py:docstring
#: of psycopg._adapters_map.AdaptersMap.register_loader:1
msgid "Configure the context to use `!loader` to convert data of oid `!oid`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.14/site-packages/psycopg/_adapters_map.py:docstring
#: of psycopg._adapters_map.AdaptersMap.register_loader:3
msgid "The PostgreSQL OID or type name to manage."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.14/site-packages/psycopg/_adapters_map.py:docstring
#: of psycopg._adapters_map.AdaptersMap.register_loader:4
msgid "The loar to register for `!oid`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.14/site-packages/psycopg/_adapters_map.py:docstring
#: of psycopg._adapters_map.AdaptersMap.register_loader:6
msgid ""
"If `oid` is specified as string, it refers to a type name, which is looked "
"up in the `types` registry."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../api/adapt.rst:83
msgid ""
"The object where to look up for types information (such as the mapping "
"between type names and oids in the specified context)."
msgstr ""

